00:02:47,039 --> 00:02:49,518
will take practice, but as time goes on,

101
00:02:48,719 --> 00:02:51,359
you're going to find that this

102
00:02:49,519 --> 00:02:52,878
mindfulness really pays off in the time

103
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:53,1000
it saves you and the clarity it gives

104
00:02:52,878 --> 00:02:55,758
you when you're looking at your book.

105
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,120
So, once you've gauged those classes and

106
00:02:55,759 --> 00:02:58,318
figured out the type of information you

107
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:59,680
want to pull from your reading, how do

108
00:02:58,318 --> 00:03:01,119
you actually go about doing that

109
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:02,878
reading? Well, to start out, let me give

110
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:05,120
you a universal tip that applies to any

111
00:03:02,878 --> 00:03:06,878
reading you do, and it's this. Don't

112
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:08,800
read your textbooks like you read a

113
00:03:06,878 --> 00:03:10,639
newspaper. People who read the newspaper

114
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:11,679
aren't reading to apply what they're

115
00:03:10,639 --> 00:03:13,279
learning. They're just reading to get

116
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:14,800
the gist of the day's events. You're not

117
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:16,400
reading for gists. You're reading for

118
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:17,440
application. Also, don't expect that

119
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:19,279
you're going to learn efficiently by

120
00:03:17,439 --> 00:03:20,878
just reading and rereading passages over

121
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:22,719
and over again. The writer Virginia

122
00:03:20,878 --> 00:03:24,878
Folks said that how often you read

123
00:03:22,719 --> 00:03:26,957
something is immaterial. How you read it

124
00:03:24,878 --> 00:03:28,559
is crucial. Think of a book like an art

125
00:03:26,959 --> 00:03:30,159
